    "It would be difficult to conclude without further experimentation.",
    "In some scenarios, it may be sufficient to detect the anomaly at a later stage, and in others, it requires to be detected in the same stage.",
    "For example, if pump P101 is running above its safe rpm, it might cause the adjacent (following) pipe to burst, affecting the plant and personnel.",
    "Where such a concern exists, the design has to include a pressure sensor.",
    "When there is a risk the pressure sensor reading is spoofed, a physical pressure safety (release) valve will have to be incorporated into the design [25]."
